# lspci - list all PCI devices.
# lspci is a utility for displaying information about PCI buses in the system and devices connecte to them.

# Show a tree-liked diagram containing all buses, bridges, devices and connections between them.
$ lspci -t

# Be verbose and display detailed information about all devices.
$ lspci -v

# Show kernel drivers handling each device and also kernel modules capable of handling it.
$ lspci -k

